This paper deals with privacy-preserving link prediction in social networks, which involves analyzing the structure of the network to predict future links while protecting the privacy of individual users. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including social network analysis (cs.SI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), databases (cs.DB), and cybernetics (cs.CY). However, given the focus on privacy and differential privacy techniques, cs.SI and cs.CR are the most likely categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.DB, and cs.CY.
